icID=200.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Suggestion for a travel-buddy-pet...</span><hr size=1> (I'm kind of in a rut, haven't played EQ in 5 weeks now, but that doesn't stop the mind from ticking...)<br>
<br>
I've been reading a lot about lack of defensive spells recently.<br>
<br>
What would you say to something along the folowing:<br>
<br>
* Mages get a spell every 12 levels, like we do with the Focus Items now.<br>
* Each spell Summons a wand, LORE, NO DROP.  Casting time would be 14 sec to summon, maybe 1 Malachite used as a component.<br>
* The Wand contains 1 charge of Summon Defensive Pet, zero-time right-click, no components used.<br>
<br>
The theory here is:  You know you're going to travel a fair distance without a pet.  Instead, you spend your time up-front ... casting time / mana to make a &quot;stored&quot; pet.  You can then go on your trip, where you may or may not run into any encounters.  If you do encounter an NPC, you have an single-use instant-cast defense, a pet that would draw the attention of the monster long enough for you to gate away without being slain.<br>
<br>
The trick is devising a pet that is fair to use in a defensive situation that wont make it overpowering in group-play...  Maybe a pet that proc's a hate-increasing spell, but only hits for 1 dmg a round...<br>
<br>
Comments?<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eelrond>Eelrond</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#333333>(5/14/02 8:17:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=200.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestion for a travel-buddy-pet...</span><hr size=1> Great idea.  And the pet should have a MEGA taunt and maybe half the hp of a fire pet.  This would give you a chance to at least get gate off <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Eelrond <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rhasinfirestorm>Rhasin Firestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 702<br> <font color=#333333>(5/15/02 2:49:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=200.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestion for a travel-buddy-pet...</span><hr size=1> How about a pet that won't attack, but chain casts (with a recast delay) a PBAoE hate increasing spell.<br>
<br>
Of course, this could be DDD, but *shrug* I guess it's an uber solo tool, not a real decoy. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886">Rhasin Firestorm</A><BR>
Conjurer of the 57th Season<BR>
Prexus</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uznailvh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#333333>(5/15/02 1:16:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=200.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestion for a travel-buddy-pet...</span><hr size=1> It doesnt have to be instant as that would actualy make it better then any other class resque spell. 3 seconds would balance it quite nicely compared to other spells. I think its a good idea, at least good enuff to send to verant. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uaristodemos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aristodemos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(5/21/02 7:51:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=200.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestion for a travel buddy-pet...</span><hr size=1> How about they just make the pets zone???  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eriol>Eriol</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#333333>(5/21/02 9:15:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=200.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestion for a travel-buddy-pet...</span><hr size=1> I think the general idea is sound.  Making it on an item instead of just a spell makes it fairly useless for chain-casting in battle situations.  Basically just having enough time to either gate, or get a really good head start running is what we really need.<br>
<br>
I like Znail_Vh's suggestion for having the staff have a casting time.  Make it about 1.5-2.0 though, since wizzies and enchanters can have their absorbtion spells up ahead of time, and necros get feign, which is 1.5 casting time (I think).  So ours should fall somewhere in between.  3.0 is a bit long in my opinion.  But I think zero is a bit much.<br>
<br>
But I agree that it's at least good enough to send in.  You never know.  It could happen.  I hope SOMETHING in the realm of escape does happen.<br>
 <p>Eriol Telcontar - Dragons Revolt<BR>
Magician of the 39th Summoning<BR>
The Tribunal</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uznailvh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 103<br> <font color=#333333>(5/22/02 5:23:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=200.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestion for a travel-buddy-pet...</span><hr size=1> The reason I suggested a little longer casting time then root, snare and fiegn is that they can all fail (be resisted) even if you get the spell off. Most of the time so are those kind of spells cast while a mob it is running towards you and you only get hit if it fails, and will then need the short cast time to channel. The pet wont fail to summon so in most cases so wont the casting time matter that much. Making it 3 seconds is good enuff to use, and it will avoid making the spell idea obviously better then other classes spells.<br>
<br>
One idea for an instant version of this would be as an AA skill with reuse timer. I think that would be both fun and not terribly unbalanced. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wezloc>WEZLOC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 707<br> <font color=#333333>(5/22/02 11:36:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=200.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestion for a travel-buddy-pet...</span><hr size=1> I think the idea is one of the better ones that has been mentioned over the past few months. However i honestly think it is a waste of time. Any defense pet needs to have the restriction lifted so that you can summon it while a pet is up. If it is truly defensive then we should be able to use it whenever the need for defense comes up. If we get a add on pull and we see that our pet isn't going to live long enough to kill the second mob then we should be able to summon that defensive pet to hold mobs at bay for at least 8 to 10secs so we can gate or make a new pet.<br>
<br>
Allowing pets to do the following is much easier to do and makes much more sense then a new spell line.<br>
<br>
Allow us to invis and keep our pets. Also allow us to invis our pets. (still trying to figure out how this could be used as a exploit.)<br>
<br>
Allow pets to zone like BST pets and familiars.<br>
<br>
Allow pets not to poof after we go LD and always be there when we log on just like familiar pets.<br>
<br>
We are suppose to be the supreme pet class. So give us the tools so that we do our intended job well.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uteng234.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Teng234</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(5/22/02 11:46:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=200.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestion for a travel-buddy-pet...</span><hr size=1> Wouldn't Being able to run around invisi with a pet up be rather uber in a PVP situation?  Unless the target had see invisi.... he/she would be at a severe disadvantage....<br>
<br>
Just a thought.<br>
<br>
Teng Voltaires<br>
57 Gnome<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eriol>Eriol</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#333333>(5/22/02 7:18:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=200.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestion for a travel-buddy-pet...</span><hr size=1> I don't think it should be an AA ability if anything like this ever happens.  Anything on AAs makes it very exclusive to the upper teirs only.  Something to help out travelling is best used by lower levels, not upper.<br>
